Package szakacs.kpi.fei.tuke.intrfc.misc

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ActorClassInfo
    A value object containing some information used for rendering actors of a particular class.
    ActorRectangle
    An extension of the base Rectangle interface providing added actor-specific functionality.
    GameConfig
    The interface of any object which stores initial game configuration data retrieved from an external storage source.
    GameConfigProcessor
    Interface implemented by any class that is responsible for extracting game configuration at application start and transforming it into Java value objects for use by the game manager.
    GameRenderer
    Created by developer on 24.1.2017.
    GameResult
    Containing information about the results (score etc.) of a particular player class for either one level or for the whole game.
    GameResults
    A value object containing GameResult objects describing the results (score etc.) for each player class during the whole game and for each level.
    GameWorldPrototype
    Created by developer on 29.1.2017.
    Queue<T>
    The interface for a generic Queue collection whose elements are of type T.
    Rectangle
    A descriptor of a rendered game object based on a mathematical rectangle.
    Stack<T>
    The interface for a generic Stack collection whose elements are of type T.
    UnregisteredActorInfo
    A value object containing information about an actor instance that has been removed from the game.
